# Markdown the lint gate deliberately does not check, auto-discovered by
# markdownlint from the repo root. Managed by shipit — a local edit surfaces
# as an OVERRIDE at the next `shipit install` reconcile. Only shipit-managed
# paths belong here; markdown authored by the consumer is the consumer's own
# to lint.
#
#   - AGENTS.md — carries the shipit-managed agents block, regenerated by
#     `shipit install`, so linting it is the generator's job.
#
# The .shipit-skills/ tree is deliberately NOT exempt (#777, relocated #921):
# every file under it is a shipit-managed unit shipped into every consumer, so it
# must pass the very markdownlint config it ships — install self-cert lints the delivered skill
# files, and this repo lints them at source, closing the class where a bare
# fence or a split ordered list (MD040/MD029) rides the managed set into a
# consumer's gate. The genre's inline HTML tags (<what-to-do>, …) and h1-less
# fragments are already accommodated by the managed markdownlint.yaml (MD033
# and MD041 off), so the prose rules do not miscategorize skill content.
#
# Generated lex projections need NO entry here: `shipit lint` never routes a
# tracked X.md whose X.lex source is tracked to markdownlint (the lexd leg
# gates the source).
AGENTS.md
# Test-data directories (issue #500): markdown fixtures / goldens / snapshots
# are deliberately-malformed or byte-exact test inputs, not prose — flagging
# them is noise about a test, not signal about a document. These are the same
# conventions `shipit lint --fix` refuses to auto-rewrite
# (lint.PROTECTED_TESTDATA_GLOBS); listing them here also spares check mode. A
# directory pattern floats to any depth and drops its whole subtree.
fixtures/
__fixtures__/
testdata/
golden/
goldens/
snapshots/
__snapshots__/
